 </DL>
<P>
<DL>
<DT><IMG WIDTH=20 HEIGHT=20 SRC="http://www-stat.wharton.upenn.edu/~waterman/icons/bluepin.gif" ALT="*"><DD><H2>
<A NAME="predict">
Prediction discussion.</A></H2>
<DT><IMG WIDTH=20 HEIGHT=20 SRC="http://www-stat.wharton.upenn.edu/~waterman/icons/bluepin.gif" ALT="*"><DD>Two types corresponding to the ``data = signal + noise'' paradigm.
<DT><IMG WIDTH=20 HEIGHT=20 SRC="http://www-stat.wharton.upenn.edu/~waterman/icons/bluepin.gif" ALT="*"><DD>Prediction of just the signal <B>or</B> prediction that also includes the
noise.
<DT><IMG WIDTH=20 HEIGHT=20 SRC="http://www-stat.wharton.upenn.edu/~waterman/icons/bluepin.gif" ALT="*"><DD>Prediction in the range of the data (interpolation) is pretty safe.
<DT><IMG WIDTH=20 HEIGHT=20 SRC="http://www-stat.wharton.upenn.edu/~waterman/icons/bluepin.gif" ALT="*"><DD>Prediction out of the range of the data (extrapolation) is pretty dangerous.
<DT><IMG WIDTH=20 HEIGHT=20 SRC="http://www-stat.wharton.upenn.edu/~waterman/icons/bluepin.gif" ALT="*"><DD>Prediction for a <B>new</B> observation has 3 sources of uncertainty.
  <DL >
    <DT><IMG WIDTH=20 HEIGHT=20 SRC="http://www-stat.wharton.upenn.edu/~waterman/icons/redpin.gif" ALT="*"><DD>The fit is not quite right - uncertainty in the true regression 
          line.
    <DT><IMG WIDTH=20 HEIGHT=20 SRC="http://www-stat.wharton.upenn.edu/~waterman/icons/redpin.gif" ALT="*"><DD>There's variability about the regression line - noise.
    <DT><IMG WIDTH=20 HEIGHT=20 SRC="http://www-stat.wharton.upenn.edu/~waterman/icons/redpin.gif" ALT="*"><DD>There is uncertainty because this may not be the correct model -
        model misspecification.
<P>
 </DL> 
 </DL></P></P><BR> <HR>
